<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1 Missing, 26 Injured in House Explosion in Marseille </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 20 (Xinhua) -- One person is missing and 26 people
were lightly injured today in an explosion that took place at a
seven-story housing building in central Marseille.
</P>
<P>
Agence France Presse reported that three lowest floors of the
building collapsed completely in the powerful explosion whose
cause remained undetermined yet, but police put gas leak as the
most probable cause.
</P>
<P>
The mayor's office has set up a special team on the site, and
some 60 people who lived in the house have been given shelters,
while all 26 injured in the explosion are hospitalized.
</P>
<P>
Firemen said the searching for a 40-year-old man still missing
is going on with difficulty, but they said the chances that he is
still alive are big. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
