<DOCNO> XIE19960721.0002 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-20 15:53 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rafsanjani to Visit Turkey in Autumn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani is going to visit Turkey in autumn in a bid to mend
ties between the two neighboring countries, a press report said
here today.
</P>
<P>
The Persian evening paper +Ettellat+ reported that President
Rafsanjani had sent separate messages to Turkish President
Sulleiman Demirel, and Prime Minister Necmettin Erbakan who heads
the pro-Islamic Welfare Party.
</P>
<P>
The report said the new Turkish prime minister is going to
visit Tehran at the invitation by President Rafsanjani.
</P>
<P>
However, the report gave no specific dates for the visits of
the Iranian president and the Turkish prime minister.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian press reported that the Turkish prime minister was
unhappy with the present state of Tehran-Ankara relations, which
have turned ice-cold since Turkey signed a military accord with
Israel early this year.
</P>
<P>
In his message to President Sulleiman Demirel, Rafsanjani
stressed the common interests and deep cultural ties between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian president also called for continued dialogue and
consultations between the two sides, a vehicle of peace and
stability in the region as he termed.
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani also expressed Iran's pleasure at the formation of
the new Turkish government headed by Erbakan and stressed the
importance of expaning ties with Islamic and neighboring
countries.
</P>
<P>
However, he pointed to the recent "unpleasant incidents" in the
border regions of the two countries, expressing confidence that
Demirel's special policy and insight would prevent the repetition
of such incidents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
