<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt to Build Giant Oil-Processing Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Egypt will soon build a giant
project to process crude oil extracted from oil fields in western
desert into petroleum products, Minister of Oil Hamdy el-Banbi
said today.
</P>
<P>
The project, to be situated in the Mediterranean port city of
Alexandria, will be part of the country's efforts to increase oil
revenues, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to produce 39,000 tons of butane gas,
256,000 tons of solar and 9,300 tons of naphtha a year, according
to Sameh Fahmi Said, Deputy Chairman of the Egyptian General
Petroleum Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The project, which will cost a total of 350 million Egyptian
pounds (100 million U.S. dollars), is expected to be finished in
42 months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
