<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Polish Woman Shooter Wins Atlanta Olympic First Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Sharpshooter Renata Mauer of
Poland became the first champion of the 26th Olympic Games by
winning the women's 10 meters air rifle event at the Wolf Creek
Shooting Complex here Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
Mauer, 27, collected 497.6 points to beat top favorite Petra
Horneber of Germany who scored a total of 497.4 points. Aleksandra
Ivosev of Yugoslavia won the bronze medal by totalling 497.2
points.
</P>
<P>
The Polish sharpshooter, who studies economics in the Wroclaw
Economics College, joined the national team 10 years ago. She
appered in international shooting stage in earlier 90s when she
took the title at the World Cup tournament in 1992 in Munich,
Germany.
</P>
<P>
At the 1992 Barcelona Olympic Games, the 1.55 meter tall
markswoman finished 17th and failed to enter the grand final in
her first Olympic competition.
</P>
<P>
When asked about her hobby, Mauer said she enjoyed travelling
and reading good books in her spare time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
