<HEADLINE> U.N. Report Reveals Britain as Most Unequal Western Country </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Britain is now the most unequal
country in the Western world with an increasingly widening gap
between the rich and poor, said a United Nations report carried in
today's Sunday Times newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Inequality in Britain has grown sharply over the past few years
and the poor now have to "live on much the same incomes as their
equivalents" in some developing countries, said the U.N. Human
Development Report.
</P>
<P>
"The United Kingdom, unfortunately, has an exceptionally high
degree of inequality," the report said.
</P>
<P>
The poorest 40 percent of the British people share only 14.6
percent of the national wealth, much lower than any other Western
country, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Statistics of the report show that the richest fifth of Britons
enjoy, on average, incomes 10 times as high as those of the
poorest fifth.
</P>
<P>
Comparison with earlier Human Development Reports also
indicates that inequality has been growing very fast in Britain,
which was ranked around middle of the industrialized countries for
the gap between the incomes of the richest and poorest fifth in
1991.
</P>
<P>
In the 1991 report, the richest fifth of Britons had incomes
6.8 times as much as those of the the poorest fifth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
