<HEADLINE> CAAC Achieves Transport Flight Safety for 24 Months Running </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The Civil Aviation Administration
of China (CAAC) recorded safe transport flights for 24 consecutive
months as of yesterday.
</P>
<P>
CAAC has conducted safe operations involving 1.8 million flight
hours over the past two years, which constitutes the longest safe
flight period for CAAC since 1982, a CAAC source said.
</P>
<P>
The CAAC has made progress in improving safe operations,
signalling an overall enhancement of the administration's flight
safety, the source added.  
</P>
