<HEADLINE> Central Working Group Directing Flood-Relief Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- A group authorized by the CPC
Central Committee and the State Council has been sent to
flood-stricken Hunan Province in central China to direct relief
efforts and extend support to the flood victims there.
</P>
<P>
The group, headed by Minister of Water Resources Niu Maosheng,
consists of senior officials from several ministries.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by Hunan Province Governor Yang Zhengwu, the group
toured the province's hardest-hit cities of Changde and Yiyang
between July 17-20.
</P>
<P>
Members drafted measures for flood relief and offered field
guidance to the relief and rescue workers.
</P>
<P>
Niu Maosheng expressed sympathy and solicitude, on behalf of
President Jiang Zemin and Premier Li Peng, for the local people
and the People's Liberation Army officers and soldiers, armed
police and public security force who are at the forefront of the
fight against the floods.
</P>
<P>
Niu urged local authorities to move quickly to save the lives
and property of the flood-besieged people and to provide the
victims with adequate food, drinking water, clothes and proper
medical treatment.
</P>
<P>
He also called on the local people to keep their morale high as
they work to rebuild their homes and resume production. 
</P>
</TEXT>
