<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Four Auto Production Bases Set up in Xiangfan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Five years after development work
began, four auto industry bases have been set up in Xiangfan
Automotive Industry Development Zone in central China's Hubei
Province.
</P>
<P>
Using an investment of two billion yuan (about 241 million US
dollars), the zone has established an auto power base, a
light-duty vehicle base, an auto parts production base, and a
research and development base for light-duty cars, covering a
total area of 955,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
The power base, which includes auto power, diesel engine and
casting plants, provides equipment for the Dongfeng and Shennong
companies.
</P>
<P>
The light-duty vehicle base is undertaking a project involving
two billion yuan (about 241 million US dollars) in investment,
that will soon form an annual production capacity of 150,000
vehicles.
</P>
<P>
In the auto parts production base, the Shenlong Auto Main
Engine Processing Plant, a Sino-French project, is expected to
equip 300,000 automobiles a year. The plant is currently capable
of producing parts for 150,000 automobiles annually.
</P>
<P>
Dongfeng Company's light-duty vehicle research and development
center, the largest of its kind, has been set up in the
development zone.
</P>
<P>
The new zone has become a vital auto production base in central
China. So far, 110 enterprises involving 69 projects have been
established there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
