<HEADLINE> Jilin Imports Global One Information System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Jilin Province of Northeast China
will import an advanced information dispatching system from Global
One Company, one of the global telecommunications leaders jointly
launched by US Sprint, French Telecom and German Telecom.
</P>
<P>
The system consists three separate parts for E-Mail, fax
storage and dispatching, and X400 information exchange, according
to the "People's Posts and Telecommunications Daily."
</P>
<P>
The X400 information exchange system is based on a platform
composed of Avian 500 switching machines, which are supplied by
the US-based Data General Co.
</P>
<P>
So far, the Global One systems have been installed in telecom
networks in the cities of Beijing and Shanghai, and Guangdong,
Jiangsu, Liaoning and Fujian provinces, and the Ministry of
Railway, the paper said. 
</P>
