<HEADLINE> IBM Launches Road Show in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The global leader of the computer
industry, IBM, launched a road show to promote its Pentium
processor-based personal computers in 18 Chinese cities.
</P>
<P>
The road show, the largest traveling exhibition held by foreign
computer makers in China, began in late June and will finish
August 31, according to the "People's Posts and Telecommunications
News."
</P>
<P>
The exhibition route includes ten provincial capitals and eight
economically-developed cities such as Xiamen, Ningbo and Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
On display during the show will be IBM PC products, including
the commercial-used desktop, laptop, PC server and consumer
multi-media computer.
</P>
<P>
IBM led China's PC market in the fourth quarter of 1995, and
has since maintained rigorous growth in the country, beating out
Compaq, a major American PC supplier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
