<HEADLINE> European Union Urges Pakistan to Diversify Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan must diversify its
exports to the European Union (EU) to maintain its share of trade
on the European market, a visiting senior EU official said here
today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference here this afternoon, Manuel
Marin, vice president of the European Union (EU), said that
Pakistan's exports to the EU concentrated on only three items
including textile, garment and leather.
</P>
<P>
"Pakistan needs to diversify its industrial production and
exports to the European market as it will be in open competition
with other exporters of textile, garments and leather in the next
few years," Marin said.
</P>
<P>
"In the next five to ten years, all elements of the World Trade
Organization agreement will be in force and Pakistan will be in
the open competition," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
He urged the Pakistani government to provide economic and
financial assistance to other industries to create opportunities.
</P>
<P>
During his three-day visit to Pakistan, Marin had discussions
with Pakistani leaders on the matters relating to signing a new
accord of cooperation between Pakistan and the European Commission
(EC).
</P>
<P>
"We want to upgrade the economic relations between the EU and
Pakistan," he said.
</P>
<P>
The EU, the largest trading partner of Pakistan, digested 27.5
percent of Pakistan's total exports in the 1995-96 fiscal year
starting from July 1, 1995.  
</P>
