<HEADLINE> Beijing Re-allots Houses Controlled by Wang Baosen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The investigation into the
criminal case involving the appropriation of public residences for
private use by Beijing's former vice-mayor Wang Baosen, has ended.
</P>
<P>
The residences were confiscated by the municipal government and
given to about 76 people with inadequate housing, including model
and advanced workers, and democratic and noted figures.
</P>
<P>
According to a municipal source, Wang illegally obtained 116
residences for private use and distribution between July 1988 and
April 1995.
</P>
<P>
The source said that Wang took these houses either by purchases
with public funds or by holding up houses which should have been
allotted to ordinary cadres and workers.
</P>
<P>
Upon exposure of Wang's criminal acts, the Beijing municipal
Party committee and government formed a special working group to
track down and retrieve the residences.  
</P>
