<HEADLINE> EU, Pakistan to Upgrade Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The economic cooperation between
the European Union (EU) and Pakistan will be upgraded, a visiting
senior EU official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Talking to newsmen at the Pakistani Foreign Office this
afternoon, EU Vice President Manuel Marin said, "last year, the
total export of Pakistan to the EU got an increase of 25 percent."
</P>
<P>
However, the total export volume which stood less than 2
billion US dollars was modest, Marin said, adding that both the EU
and Pakistan expressed the hope to further increase the bilateral
trade.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan's export to the EU concentrated on three items
including textile, garment and leather, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Pakistan is a country which plays an important role in this
region and in the Islamic world," he added.
</P>
<P>
So, the EU is willing to enhance its cooperation with Pakistan
in more fields, he said, adding that both sides will create more
opportunities and possibilities in the bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said that the EU has submitted to the European Commission a
detailed mandate of new cooperation and partnership between the EU
and Pakistan, which is expected to be singed early next year.
</P>
<P>
During his three-day visit in Pakistan, Marin held talks with
the Pakistani president, the prime minister and other senior
government officials on various issues of common interest.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani Foreign Minister Sardar Aseff Ahmed Ali today spoke
highly of the Marin's visit.
</P>
<P>
He said, "this is the first time for high-level contacts
between Pakistan and the EU."
</P>
<P>
All the meetings between Marin and Pakistani senior officials
were "creative, productive and satisfactory."
</P>
<P>
Although there were still some problems which needed to be
solved through discussion, Pakistan was encouraged to strengthen
its cooperation with the EU, he stressed.  
