<HEADLINE> SLA Prisoners Freed by Hezbollah Arrive in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kafr Tibnit, Lebanon, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Seventeen prisoners
of the militia of the South Lebanese Army (SLA) set free by
Hezbollah arrived here as part of the swap of prisoners and
remains between Hezbollah and Israel in 14 years.
</P>
<P>
The hand-over ceremony will be conducted in the presence of the
International Red Cross Committee (IRCC) at a square in the
village.
</P>
<P>
The 17 prisoners were ferried here in nine vehicles of the
IRCC, which are parked at the eastern entrance of the village Kafr
Tibnit, which is situated on the Israeli-Lebanese border in the
Israeli self-claimed "Security Zone" in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The IRCC officials, who arrived here at 8:00 local time (0500
GMT) in 50 ambulances of the Red Cross, are awaiting the arrival
of the prisoners set free by Israel so as to conduct the ceremony
of swapping prisoners between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
An IRCC spokesman told Xinhua that the 17 prisoners were handed
over to them by the Lebanese authorities in Beirut this morning.
</P>
<P>
Asked whether there are the remains of two Israeli soldiers in
the convoy, the spokesman said that this morning the Lebanese
authorities sent two coffins to the IRCC, which in turn handed
them to a German delegation at the Beirut airport.
</P>
<P>
He said it is unclear for the time being whether the two
coffins contained the remains of the Israeli soldiers. "We are not
part of the arrangement. We are only responsible for the transfer,"
he said, adding that it is not their responsibility to identify the
prisoners and remains.
</P>
<P>
A thin-faced SLA prisoner told Xinhua that he is 30 and has
been held by Hezbollah for two years and eight months. He also
said the jail terms vary considerably for the prisoners.
</P>
<P>
He refused to reveal his name, saying that all of the prisoners
were told not to answer questions by reporters.
</P>
<P>
The 17 prisoners sat in four ambulances, and are forbidden
to go out of the vehicles before the hand-over ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Several bearded youths attempted to pass the security line
by police, resulting in a minor conflict with the police. The two
sides exchanged kicks and blows, but no one was injured.
</P>
<P>
Israel will also hand over 45 prisoners to Lebanon. The
prisoners were jailed at Khiam deeply inside the Israeli
self-proclaimed "security zone" in south Lebanon,
</P>
<P>
As Hezbollah called on the families of the dead soldiers to
converge in the village today, about 3,000 of them arrived by 9:00
a.m. (0600 GMT) and many more continued to arrive in the village.
</P>
<P>
According to Red Cross officials, only nine of the 150 remains
have been identified. 
</P>
</TEXT>
