<HEADLINE> Arab Center for Water Resources Studies to be </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League (AL) has decided
to establish an Arab center for water resources studies and water
security in Syria's capital Damascus, it was announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The center is intended to tackle issues and problems related to
Arab water resources and to undergo technical and legal research
on the resources.
</P>
<P>
According to official sources at Syria's Irrigation Ministry,
Syria will provide all the facilities necessary for the center
including a residence, provided that the Arab League will bear
the research expenses and wages of technical experts and other
personnel who are going to work at the center.
</P>
<P>
Most Arab countries in the region have to share water resources
with their neighboring countries. The establishment of such a
center is widely believed here very conducive to solving problems
caused by water-sharing. 
</P>
