<HEADLINE> Shanghai Enterprises Seek Help from Short-term Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Enterprises in Shanghai are
raising an increasing amount of capital by issuing short-term
bonds, which totaled nearly one billion yuan in the first half of
this year.
</P>
<P>
The money went to 83 local firms, including 13 listed in the
stock market, considerably relieving their shortages of operating
funds, according to the Shanghai branch of the People's Bank of
China.
</P>
<P>
With a tight monetary policy, the bank could not provide
sufficient indirect financing for the businesses. Thus, short-term
bonds have proved to be an effective way for raising operating
capital.
</P>
<P>
Last year, short-term bonds brought in almost 1.8 billion yuan
in new capital.
</P>
<P>
Almost 800 enterprises have issued short-term bonds in Shanghai
since 1987, raising a total of 10 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
