<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Alatas: 29th AMM, Most fruitful Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian Foreign Minister Ali
Alatas said here today that the 29th Ministerial Meeting of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) broke new ground as
it forged ahead in the directions set forth by the ASEAN leaders
and has been a most fruitful meeting -- an appropriate finale to a
watershed year.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the closing ceremony of the two-day meeting
attended by all the seven ASEAN members, Alatas said that the
joint communique which emanated from the meeting addressed a broad
range of issues and common concerns and manifested ASEAN's firm
resolve to carry out decisions taken by its leaders during the
fifth summit in Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
Alatas, who is also chairman of the ASEAN's annual meeting,
said that "We have moved considerably closer to the realization of
a Zone of Peace, Freedom and Neutrality (ZOPFAN), a development
made possible by the fact that the Treaty of Amity and Cooperation
(TAC) and the Treaty on the Southeast Asia Nuclear-Free Zone have
already been signed by all ten countries of Southeast Asia."
</P>
<P>
The meeting adopted a set of criteria for participation in the
ASEAN Regional Forum (ARF).
</P>
<P>
In view of the keen interest of many countries outside the
region to participate in the exchange of views and information on
political and security matters that take place in this Forum,
Alatas expected that the ARF process will advance much further.
</P>
<P>
In the economic field, he said, the meeting has focused on the
theme of "greater economic integration" and thereby accelerated
and deepened its common commitments under the ASEAN Free Trade
Area (AFTA).
</P>
<P>
ASEAN has also expanded its economic cooperation into new
sectors and strengthened its linkages with economies within the
region and beyond, he added.
</P>
<P>
Following the AMM, the third ARF meeting and the annual Post
Ministerial Conference (PMC) will be held here from July 23 to 25.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
