<HEADLINE> 17 Gold Medals for Grab in Atlanta Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- A total of 17 new champions will be
produced here as the 26th Olympic Games swing into second-day
competition here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Two gold medals are expected from shooting, the same as
Saturday's, in the women's air pistol and men's trap. Bulgaria's
European champion Maria Grozdeva and Jasna Sekaric of Yugoslavia
are favorites in the women's section.
</P>
<P>
Cyclying will have its first gold medal decided in the women's road
race in which Australia's Kathryn Watt will defend her title
against the French onslaught led by 10-time world champion
Jeannie Longo-Ciprelli.
</P>
<P>
Four more golds will be contested in the Olympic swimming
pool where a new world record was created Saturday in the men's
100m breaststroke. Today's program includes finals in the
women's 200m freestyle and 100m breaststroke and the men's 400m
individual medley and 4x200m freestyle medley.
</P>
<P>
Wreslting will give birth to five champions today in the
Greco-Roman 48kg, 57kg, 68kg, 82kg and 100kg categories.
</P>
<P>
Two more golds each will come out of the fencing and judo
sports while weightlifting will offer another gold medal in the
59kg discipline.
</P>
<P>
Action will also unfold in the equestrian, softball and rowing
events as well as baseball, basketball, hockey, gymnastics,
soccer, water polo and volleyball. 
</P>
