<HEADLINE> Official Asks Entertainment Industry to Serve Common Folks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 21 (Xinhua) -- A senior official with the
Ministry of Culture has asked the country's entertainment industry
to serve the ordinary people, instead of pleasing a small group of
well-off along, according to the China Culture News.
</P>
<P>
Meng Xiaosi, an official in charge of the cultural market,
attributed the recent slump in the recreation industry to
"irrational development", the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, there are more than 170,000 places of
recreation across the country, but most of them only cater to the
needs of "big shots" or the rich, Meng noted.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Culture will strengthen control of the culture
market and the entertainment industry so as to ensure better
service for the ordinary people, according to Meng.
</P>
<P>
Also, the government will push ahead with the crackdown on
pornographic and other unhealthy tendencies, Meng said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
