<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Reduces Duty on Import of Rice from Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) has
agreed to reduce 50 percent of the duty on its import of rice from
Pakistan, a visiting senior EU official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference here this afternoon, EU Vice
President Manuel Marin said that the reduction solved a negative
point in the trade between the EU and Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Marin said that Pakistan had criticized the EU for levying
higher duty on its import of rice from Pakistan than that from
India.
</P>
<P>
Marin admitted that it was a kind of "discrimination" to
Pakistan and said, "now we have found a common solution."
</P>
<P>
According to an agreement in this regard, the duty on the EU
import of rice from Pakistan will be reduced to nearly 190 US
dollars per ton from 380 dollars per ton previously.
</P>
<P>
India will also pay 190 dollars per ton for its export of rice
to the EU.
</P>
<P>
Marin arrived here Friday on a three-day visit to Pakistan.
During his visit, he held talks with senior Pakistani government
officials on various issues of common interest.
</P>
<P>
The EU is Pakistan's largest trading partner which enjoyed 27.5
percent of Pakistan's international trade from July 1, 1995 to
June 30, 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
