<HEADLINE> Demand of Paper to Increase in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Demand for paper in China will
reach 30 to 34 million tons by the end of the century, the State
Light Industry Association has predicted.
</P>
<P>
The Township Enterprise Daily quoted the association as
predicting that demand for newspaper will be more than 1.1 million
tons and that for book print will be 2.6 million tons.
</P>
<P>
China now has 5,600 paper plants, producing 21.4 million tons
of paper each year, ranking the third in the world.
</P>
<P>
However, the Beijing-based daily noted that due to backward
technology, half of the paper produced is of low grade, falling
short of the changing market demand.
</P>
<P>
By the year 2005, paper consumption in China is believed to be
around 40 million tons.  
</P>
</TEXT>
