<HEADLINE> FMs Welcomes Proposal for ASEAN Common Time Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Foreign ministers of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) today welcomed an
initiative of ASEAN economic ministers to discuss the proposal for
an ASEAN common time zone.
</P>
<P>
While Indonesia, Thailand and Vietnam have their standard times
as GMT plus seven hours, the other ASEAN member countries --
Brunei, Malaysia, Singapore and the Philippines -- have theirs as
GMT plus eight hours.
</P>
<P>
In a joint communique issued at the end of their annual meeting
here, the foreign ministers said that the establishment of the
common time zone aims to facilitate the cooperative activities
among the ASEAN countries.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN's seven member countries attended the two-day ministerial
meeting, which will be followed by the ASEAN Regional Forum (ARF)
and the Post Ministerial Conference (PMC) from July 23 to 25.
</P>
