<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASEAN Reaffirms Cooperation with Partners, Observers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN) today reaffirmed its commitment to working closely
with its dialogue partners and observers, according to a joint
communique by ASEAN foreign ministers at the end of their annual
meeting here.
</P>
<P>
The communique said that ASEAN is playing an increasingly
important role in maintaining peace, stability and prosperity in
the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The ministers welcomed China, India and Russia as new dialogue
partners of ASEAN and looked forward to broader cooperation with
them, said the communique.
</P>
<P>
The admission of the three new partners has brought to 10 the
number of ASEAN's dialogue partners, which are Australia, Canada,
China, India, the European Union, Japan, New Zealand, Russia,
South Korea, and the United States.
</P>
<P>
"The relative peace and stability (in the Asia Pacific region)
could be largely attributed to the endeavors of ASEAN to cultivate
the habits of dialogue, consensus and cooperation among the
countries in the region and to encourage the solution of disputes
through negotiations and other peaceful means," they said.
</P>
<P>
However, they acknowledged that tensions still exist in the
region as well as in other parts of the world, as long-standing
disputes, if not appropriately managed, could lead to major
conflicts and threaten the regional and international stability.
</P>
<P>
The ministers praised the development of the ASEAN Regional
Forum and the closer cooperative relations between ASEAN and non
governmental bodies.  
