<HEADLINE> WTO Ministerial Conference to Be Held in Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The inaugural Ministerial
Conference (MC) of the World Trade Organization (WTO) will be held
in Singapore in December this year, foreign ministers of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) said at a two-day
meeting ending here today.
</P>
<P>
According to a joint communique issued by the meeting, the
foreign ministers recognized the importance of the Singapore MC
and reaffirmed their commitment to ensuring a substantial outcome
at the MC.
</P>
<P>
The ministers agreed that the Singapore MC should critically
review the implementation of the Uruguay Round Agreement and seek
a ministerial mandate to start the preparatory work on the
built-up agenda, including agriculture.
</P>
<P>
They said that ASEAN members should actively work for a
successful conclusion of the negotiations on basic
telecommunications and maritime transport services and urged other
WTO countries to also exert efforts to achieve that goal.
</P>
<P>
The ministers reiterated ASEAN's opposition to any attempt to
include issues not related to trade, such as corruption and social
cause, at the Singapore MC.  
</P>
