<HEADLINE> 87,000 Laid-off Workers in Fujian Re-employed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Southeast China's coastal Fujian
Province has managed to help 87,000 laid-off workers find new jobs
as part of its "re-employment project".
</P>
<P>
The project was designed to help local state-owned enterprises,
which are small but numerous and money-losing, get over
difficulties in production and find new jobs for workers to be
laid off soon.
</P>
<P>
Sanming City, which has many state-owned firms, has come up
with a series of measures to help enterprises in difficulty get
discount loans and other aid rather than unemployment relief fund
alone. The practice is conducive to helping enterprises that still
have good prospects, officials said.
</P>
<P>
In line with its principle of giving priority to helping
laid-off workers by using results of auctioned property rights of
bankrupt enterprises, the province has had satisfactory results in
getting many ailing enterprises back on their feet and
re-employing laid-off workers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
