<HEADLINE> China's Ecological Agriculture Advances </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 21 (Xinhua) -- To fight the threat to
agriculture of a worsening environment and to prevent agriculture
from harming the environment, the Chinese government has had an
ecological agriculture campaign running since the 1980s.
</P>
<P>
China has seen some economic improvements with its strategy of
sustained development and ecological agriculture, according to the
latest statistics of the Ministry of Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The government places great importance on ecological
agriculture and lists it among the government's top ten topics on
the environment and development, according to Hong Bazeng,
vice-minister of agriculture.
</P>
<P>
At present, an ecological agriculture management and technology
popularization network has taken shape at the national, provincial
and county levels.
</P>
<P>
In 1993, a joint leading group was set up by seven government
ministries and departments to monitor work in ecological
agricultural counties, where sustained development is the dominant
mode of agricultural development.
</P>
<P>
So far, seven villages and townships in China have been awarded
the title of "Global 500" by the United Nations for their success
in sustained development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
