<HEADLINE> Central Chinese City Finding Ways To Improve Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The capital of central China's
Henan Province hopes to lure larger numbers of tourists with a
combination of ancient culture and modern civilization in the next
few years.
</P>
<P>
Tourists can enjoy scenery of the Yellow River, the hometown of
Huangdi who is known as the ancestor of the Chinese nation, and
superb Chinese martial arts, as well as excellent shopping, local
tourism authorities say.
</P>
<P>
Local government is making great efforts to improve tourist
facilities, transportation conditions, and develop new tourist
attractions.
</P>
<P>
The effort is in response to a national competition to create
"top tourism cities".
</P>
<P>
Zhengzhou has more than 150 scenic spots, 44 travel services
and 29 hotels that cater to foreign tourists. It hosted 390,000
overseas and domestic visitors over the past five years,
registering a 14.8 percent of annual increase. 
