<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-FM on ASEAN's Regional Role </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 21 (Xinhua) -- China hopes that the ASEAN will
continue to make valuable contributions to the regional and global
peace, stability and economic prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan made the statement
in an interview with the "People's Daily" and Xinhua here today.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 29 years since its establishment, ASEAN has made
remarkable achievements in reinforcing the organization's
political unity and strengthening economic co-operation, Tang said.
</P>
<P>
In the current situation which sees the speeding up of
multi-polarization in the Asian-Pacific region, ASEAN is playing
an important role in maintaining regional peace and stability and
in accelerating regional economic cooperation for common
development, the vice-minister said.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN regional forum initiated by the association and the
Asia-Pacific Economic Co-operation (APEC) with ASEAN as an
initiator, have both become major channels for security dialogues
and economic cooperation of the Asian-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The first Asia-Europe Meeting convened earlier this year and
sponsored by ASEAN is playing an important role in bridging and
strengthening links and expanding cooperation between the two
continents, he noted, adding all these efforts have aroused
world-wide attention.
</P>
<P>
"We are pleased with the achievements ASEAN has made," Tang
said, expressing the hope that ASEAN will continue to make
valuable contributions to regional and world peace, stability and
economic prosperity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
