and 168 others injured in the fighting while at least 200 were
killed on the LTTE side.
</P>
<P>
Security in Colombo and nearby cities have been strengthened
following the Mullaitivu attack as the LTTE declared Black July to
commemorate the 1983 riots.
</P>
<P>
According to an Information Department release on Friday
evening, President Chandrika Kumaratunga, who left for London last
weekend with her two children on a private visit, has made
arrangements for immediate return to Sri Lanka on receiving
reports of the Mullaitivu attack.  
