Maldives needed more time to prepare, the sources pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The SAARC Summit had been postponed thrice. The fifth SAARC
Summit scheduled to be held in Sri Lanka in 1989 was called-off.
Later in 1992 the conference which was to be held in Dhaka was
called-off after the demolition of the historic Badri Mosque. And
this time, the ninth SAARC Summit Scheduled to be held in the
Maldives is also put off.
</P>
<P>
The SAARC consists of all the South Asian countries which
includes Pakistan, India, Bangladesh, Sri Lanka, The Maldives,
Nepal and Bhutan. 
