the last minutes enabled the Chinese team to win from Angola, 10th
finisher at the Barcelona Olympics, with a score of 70-67.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, hoping to raise their ranking from 12th at
the last Olympics, came from 5-19 down to tie the halftime score
at the 36-36.
</P>
<P>
The 19-year-old center Wang Zhizhi scored 17 points and gained
eight rebounds in the match. He was followed by Wu Weidong with 15
points and Sun Jun with 14.
</P>
<P>
Angola's ace players are Angelo Victoriano and Antonio
Carvalho, both scoring 13 points.
</P>
<P>
In Group A, Australia downed South Korea 111-88 after leading
64-37 at the halftime. Yugoslavia beat Greece 71-63 (30-30).
Brazil won from Puerto Rico 101-98 (58-54).
</P>
<P>
