<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-ASEAN Dialogue Partnership Promises Closer Co-op: Vice-FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan said here today that China's full dialogue partnership
with the ASEAN has ushered in a new stage in its relations with
the organization.
</P>
<P>
In response to a question concerning ASEAN's recent decision to
upgrade China as its full dialogue partner during an interview
with the "People's Daily" and Xinhua, Tang said that the move is
sure to promote overall co-operations between China and the ASEAN
in diversified fields.
</P>
<P>
Established on August 7, 1967, the ASEAN comprises Indonesia,
Malaysia, Singapore, Thailand, the Philippines, Brunei and Viet
Nam. The seven countries, Tang noted, are all important neighbors
of China and have sound diplomatic relations with China.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN launched the full dialogue partnership with the U.S.,
Japan, Australia and the European Union with a view to expanding
economic co-operation, absorbing foreign investment and
technology, and exchanging views on regional and international
issues.
</P>
<P>
China began dialogue with ASEAN in 1991 as a consultative
partner. In his letter to Ali Atalas, Chairman of the ASEAN's
Standing Committee and Indonesian Foreign Minister, in March this
year, Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen
clearly expressed China's hope to become ASEAN's full dialogue
partner.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN made an active response on June 24 when Minister Atalas
notified Qian in a letter about the consensus of ASEAN foreign
ministers to upgrade China as a full dialogue partner and invited
Qian to attend the conference between ASEAN and its dialogue
partners scheduled in late July in Jakarta.
</P>
<P>
"China's full dialogue partnership with ASEAN symbolizes that
the relations between China and the ASEAN member countries, and
the organization as a whole, have embarked on a new stage," Tang
said. The move, he believed, would help stimulate the Sino-ASEAN
co-operation in various fields. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
