<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 21 (Xinhua) 21 -- ASEAN's acceptance of Myanmar as
an observer will contribute to the maintenance of regional peace
and stability, The Mirror and The New Light of Myanmar, two
official newspapers of the country, said in their editorials
today.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar was admitted as an observer of the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) on Saturday at the 29th annual
ASEAN ministerial meeting in Jakarta, capital of Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Indonesian Foreign Minister Ali Alatas, chairman of the ASEAN
Standing Committee, said that ASEAN looks forward to closer
cooperation with Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar Foreign Minister U Ohn Gyaw said that by accepting his
country as an observer, ASEAN has made a step closer to its
ultimate goal of one Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated Myanmar's commitment to the ideals and objectives
of ASEAN, the newspapers said.
</P>
<P>
According to The New Light of Myanmar, some internal and
external "destructive elements" had tried to interfere with
ASEAN's acceptance of Myanmar and their schemes have now gone
bankrupt.
</P>
<P>
"With bilateral, multilateral and regional cooperation, there
will be greater chances for prosperity in the region," the paper
stressed. 
</P>
