<HEADLINE> Bomb Explosion at Spanish Airport Injures 33 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, July 20 (Xinhua) -- A bomb exploded today at the Reus
Airport in northeastern Spain, injuring 33, most of them British
tourists.
</P>
<P>
The Basque separatist group ETA called newspapers to warn of
four bombs just minutes before the explosion, the Efe news agency
said.
</P>
<P>
Police had begun evacuating 1,000 people from the airport when
the bomb exploded in a trash can outside a restaurant in the
passenger lounge.
</P>
<P>
The group also planted bombs at two luxury hotels in the beach
towns of Salou and Cambrills. But police evacuated the hotels,
found the explosives and detonated them, causing only minor
damages, said Alex Marti, spokesman for the Tarragona municipal
government.
</P>
<P>
ETA has killed some 800 people since it began fighting in 1968
for independence of northern Spain's Basque region. Its most
recent attacks are apparently aimed at crippling Spain's lucrative
tourist industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
