the parliament ineffective and turn it into their "own forum",
Bhuiyan said: "Our party is keen to see the present parliament as
the center of all national activities and help it play an
effective role in resolving all problems facing the nation. But
the BNP alone can't do this unless the ruling party is sincere in
doing so."
</P>
<P>
"How can the parliament become effective if the speaker
violates the rules to protect the interests of the treasury bench
members and denies the rights of the opposition lawyers?" he
asked. 
