<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Export of Aquatic Products Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's aquatic products sector
exported 67,200 tons of products for about 300 million U.S dollars
in the first six months of this year, up 12 per cent over the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam exports aquatic products to 25 countries, 75 per cent
of which to japan, singapore and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam ranks 19th in the world in aquatic production, 30th in
export earnings, and 5th in the output of shrimps.
</P>
<P>
This year, the aquatic products sector is expected to export
650 to 680 million U.S. dollars worth of aquatic products,
according to the official media today.
</P>
<P>
In its development plan to the year 2000, the sector aims to
achieve an export value of 1 to 1.1 billion U.S. dollars. 
</P>
