<HEADLINE> Wang Blows Last Shot to Finish Second in Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 20 (Xinhua) -- China's defending Olympic champion
Wang Yifu blew a 3.8 points lead at the last shot to finish second
after Italian Roberto Di Donna in the men's air pistol final of
the Olympic Games here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Poland's Renata Mauer edged out Petra Horneber of Germany
earlier in the women's 10 meters air rifle event to win the Games'
first gold medal.
</P>
<P>
The 36-year-old Wang, who have been troubled by ear
inflammation and hypoglycemia, an ailment which causes fatigue and
lack of concentration, scored 6.5 points in the last shot,
squandering a 3.8-points lead and conceding the title to Di Donna.
</P>
<P>
The Italian, who scored 10.0 points in the last shot for a
total of 684.2, just one tenth of a point better than Wang.
</P>
<P>
Tanu Kiriakov of Bulgaria finished third with 683.8.
</P>
<P>
Wang collapsed after the final shot and he was rushed into a
nearby clinic.
</P>
<P>
"Because of illness, Wang hasn't eaten anything before the
final and he has been inhaling oxygem minutes before picking up
his pistol," Chinese head coach Zhang Heng said.
</P>
<P>
"Wang told me later that he felt dizzy and then blackout after
the ninth round and he just pulled trigger blindly for the last
shot," Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
"I knew there must have been something wrong with Wang," said
Di Donna, "6.5 points is unbelievable."
</P>
<P>
The Italian, who have won the most of his encounters with Wang
in recent years, hailed Wang as "one of the greatest shooters in
history".
</P>
<P>
Mauer trailed all the way in the final until she scored 10.7
points against Horneber's 8.8 in the last shot to lift the Games'
first title.
</P>
<P>
Mauer totaled 497.6 points, followed by Horneber at 497.4 and
Yugoslav Aleksandra Ivosev's 497.2.
</P>
<P>
"I got too nervous in the last shot," said Hornber. "Pressure
was just too much."
</P>
<P>
Mauer, who finished runner-up three times in the 1995 World Cup
series, said she had gained experiences and toughened her
mentality from the international competitions she entered last
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960721.0140 </DOCNO>
