<HEADLINE> Czech Republic Reports More Crimes Committed by Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, July 20 (Xinhua) -- A total of 169 policemen in the
Czech Republic committed crimes in the first six months of this
year, an increase of 20 percent over the same period in 1995, the
local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Interior Minister Jan Ruml told the press that the actual
number of policemen committing crimes far exceeded the reported
level, saying that it is impossible to record all the crimes
committed by policemen.
</P>
<P>
There are 48,000 policemen in the country, many of whom could
not conquer the temptation of booming market economy, committing
crimes of power-abusing and bribe-taking. 
</P>
</TEXT>
