<HEADLINE> Pakistan Beats United States in Olympic Hockey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Shahbaz Ahmed laid on three goals
as Pakistan eased past host United States 4-0 in their opening
group A match on Saturday at the Centennial Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Ahmed, who arrived only on Friday after a late Olympic call up,
did not start the match but as soon as he was introduced as a
substitute, Pakistan came to life against a very defensive
American team.
</P>
<P>
In the 10th minute, he drew two defenders and his delicate
reverse stick center found the unmarked Mohammed Shahbaz who slid
the ball past Steve Wagner in the opponents' goal.
</P>
<P>
Eight minutes later it was center forward Kamran Ashraf who
profitted from his precision pass to notch the second and Pakistan
went 3-0 ahead in the 25th minute as Muhammed Sarwar crossed for
Ashraf to score his second with a reverse stick deflection.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan completed their scoring in the 62nd minute when Tahir
Zaman turned in Shahbaz's free hit.
</P>
<P>
In Group A of the women's preliminary round, Germany outplayed
Argentina 2-0 after leading 1-0 at the halftime.
</P>
<P>
Vanessa Schmoranzer Van Kooperen opened the scoring at the 16th
minute while Heike Laetzsch added the second goal in the 38th
minute. 
</P>
