<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mutlu--Goliath Crane from Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 20 (Xinhua) -- To his rivals, he is like a
mountain which could not be conquered, to his fans, he is like a
Goliath crane which could lift hundreds tons of weight.
</P>
<P>
Turk weightlifter Halil Mutlu, who has won four world gold
medals, claimed his first Olympic title here Saturday afternoon,
winning the men's 54-kg category at the Georgia World Congress
Center.
</P>
<P>
Mutlu, who has three world records of the category in hands,
had 287.5 kilograms from two lifts, beating his archrival Chinese
Zhang Xiangsen to the second by 7.5 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
"I am excited to take the Olympic gold today," he said at a
post-competition press, "It is not only a honour for me, but a
honour for five million people in my country."
</P>
<P>
Mutlu, who finished fifth in the last Olympic Games in
Barcelona four years ago, had his long-time dream come true. "The
Olympic title is very important to me. It means a lot to me," he
said.
</P>
<P>
After the International Weightlifting Federation made a change
of the ten categories in 1993, aiming to clean the name of the
sport, Mutlu began to dominate the 54-kg category since 1994.
</P>
<P>
At the 1994 World Championships in Istanbul, Turkey, Mutlu had
three world record weights to make a sweep clean of the three
events in the category.
</P>
<P>
In the 1995 World Championships in Guangzhou, China, he was
beaten by Zhang on bodyweight difference.
</P>
<P>
"I lost to him (Zhang Xiangsen) at the World Championships," he
said, "but I beat him today."
</P>
<P>
Responding on the world record lift in snatch, he said:"I did
not notice the world record, I just want lift more to win the
Olympic gold."
</P>
<P>
Mutlu, both physically and mentally strong, missed his first
attempt in jerk, but continued to make good lifts in the next two
tries. "After I failed my first lift, I just hoped to have that
weight," he said. "My first expectation here is to have an medal,
no matter gold or silver."
</P>
<P>
Chinese team manager Wang Jianwei praised Mutlu as "stable and
strong" in competition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
