<HEADLINE> Portugal Wins Olympic Soccer Opener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Two goals by Afonso Martins
enabled favorite Portugal to beat Tunisia 2-0 in a bruising
Olympic soccer opener Saturday in Washington DC.
</P>
<P>
Martins scored both goals amid a flurry of yellow and red cards
that saw both sides reduced to 10 men. He opened the scoring for
Portugal just 12 minutes into the first half of the Group C match.
</P>
<P>
Six minutes into the second half, Tunisia had the chance to
equalise through a penalty but Adel Sellim crashed the ball
against the crossbar.
</P>
<P>
In the 78th minute, Martens collected his second goal after a
horrible mistake by the Tunisian keeper.
</P>
<P>
Looking to cross the ball from a seemingly harmless position on
the left of the Tunisian penalty area, Martens saw the goalkeeper
woefully out of position and simply stroked the ball inside the
near post.
</P>
<P>
Tunisia's woes were compounded five minutes later when Riadh
Bouazizi, who had already been booked, was sent off for a clumsy
challenge on Dominguez, who had to be stretchered from the field.
</P>
<P>
Bouazizi was joined shortly in the dressing room by Portugal's
Andrade, who was shown the red card for a crunching tackle from
behind. 
</P>
</TEXT>
