<DOCNO> XIE19960721.0160 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mutlu Lifts World Record for Olympic Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Turk hercules Halil Mutlu set a
world record in snatch en route to winning the first gold medal in
weightlifting at the Centennial Olympics here Saturday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Mutlu, with three world records in hands in the men's 54-kg
category, had 132.5 kilograms in snatch, beating his own world
mark by 2.5 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
The former world champion also jerked 155 kilos for a total of
287.5, edging world title holder Zhang Xiangsen of China for the
Olympic gold.
</P>
<P>
Zhang, who beat Mutlu to second at the last world championships
in Guangzhou, China in November of 1995, ranked second at 280
kilos, with 130 from snatch and 150 from jerk.
</P>
<P>
The bronze medal went to Sevdalin Minchev of Bulgaria, who had
277.5 from two lifts.
</P>
<P>
Mutlu and Zhang had a tit-to-tat battle in the Olympic arena.
After Zhang Xiangsen iniated his weight at 122.5 kilograms, Mutlu
added the bar to 125 in his first attempt.
</P>
<P>
Zhang, with his personal best of 130 in training, asked 127.5
kilos, but only missed the weight.
</P>
<P>
After Mutlu finished 130 kilos in the second attempt, Zhang
took the risk for 130 in his last attempt.
</P>
<P>
"I have to ask the weight in my third attempt at that time,"
said Zhang afterwards. "If I succeeded, Mutlu would be forced to
ask more, as I have less bodyweight than him."
</P>
<P>
Mutlu was indeed forced to try 132.5 kilos and lifted the
weight in his last attempt for a new world record.
</P>
<P>
While in the clean and jerk, Zhang lagged far behind his Turk
rival who could jerk 165 kilograms in training.
</P>
<P>
"I could only lift 157.5 kilograms at my utmost in jerk in
training," Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
Mutlu almost had the Olympic gold slipped out of his hands when
he missed his first try at 152.5 kilos in jerk.
</P>
<P>
"At the time when he failed, I did think I may have a chance
for the title," Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
However, Mutlu, recovering from the first fall, even lifted 155
kilos in his last try.
</P>
<P>
Failing for 155 in his second attempt, Zhang tried 157.5 in the
last, a bet he had to take in order to win the Olympic title on
bodyweight difference against Mutlu.
</P>
<P>
Zhang tried hard but could only lift the bar at his chest.
</P>
<P>
Chinese team manager Wang Jianwei said, "I am glad, for he has
done his best, and and I am also sad, for he does not win."
</P>
<P>
Zhang blamed his bad lift in jerk to right arm injury. "I
injured my right arm when I lifted 130 kilos in the snatch," he
explained.
</P>
<P>
"After three months or so, my right arm would be completely
recovered," he added.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time for Zhang to take part in the Olympics. "This
time I lose, next time I may win," said 24-year-old Zhang.
</P>
<P>
Defending Olympic champion Ivan Ivanov of Bulgaria, who won the
men's 52-kg category in Barcelona four years ago, slipped down to
the eighth in Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
After the Barcelona Olympics, the International Weightlifting
Committee changed the ten categories in 1993.
</P>
<P>
The competition of 59-kg category will be held on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960721.0163 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
