<HEADLINE> Turkey Wins Its First Centennial Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Turkey won its first Atlanta
Olympic Games gold medal when strongman Halil Mutlu lifted a
total of 287.5kg in the men's 54kg class weightlifting
competition here this evening.
</P>
<P>
Multu snatched 132.5kg in his third attempt, setting a new
world record. Then he lifted 155kg in the jerk event, totalling
287.5kg for the gold medal, which is also the first for Turkey at
the current games.
</P>
<P>
World champion Zhang Xiangsen of China came second with a
two-lift total of 280kg. He snatched 130kg and jerked 150kg in
the event which drew nine competitors from seven countries.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria's Sevdalin Minchev took the bronze, snatching 125kg
and jerking 152.5kg for a total of 277.5kg. 
</P>
