<HEADLINE> First Nigeria-China Arts, Crafts Show Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 20 (Xinhua) -- The first Nigeria-China arts and
crafts exhibition opened here today at the Nigerian national
museum.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, organized by the Nigeria-China Friendship
Association, is aimed at promoting bilateral relations through
cultrual exchanges, said V.N. Chibundu, Chairman of the
association.
</P>
<P>
There is a variety of Nigerian and Chinese exhibits, including
bronze sculpture, wood and ivory carvings, artistic textiles,
Chinese paintings, drawings, bamboo articles and lacquerware.
</P>
<P>
The exhibits are provided by the Nigerian National Art
Gallery, National Council for Arts and Crafts, the Chinese
Ministry of Culture and the Chinese People's Association for
Friendship with Foreign Countries.
</P>
<P>
Chibundu, who was Nigeria's ambassador to China between
1981 and 1984, told Xinhua that a series of seminars and discussions
will be held on reviewing the bilateral relations during
the exhibition, which is to end on July 27. 
</P>
