<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ministers Emphasize Strengthening of Inter-ASEAN </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 20 (Xinhua) -- The success in economic area of
the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) has broadened
the base of cooperation among the member countries, the Indonesian
and Thai foreign ministers said here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening session of the 29th ASEAN Ministerial
Meeting (AMM), Indonesian foreign minister Ali Alatas said aside
from cooperation in tariff reduction, the inter economic
cooperation among the ASEAN countries have involved trade in
services, intellectual property rights and investments.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Thai foreign minister said inter-ASEAN trade and
foreign direct investment have increased significantly. According
to him, the inter trade reached 70 billion US. dollars in 1995, of
which common effective preferential tariff (CEPT) and ASEAN Free
Trade Area products (AFTA) accounted for some 60 billion US.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN member countries have phased in over 45,000 items,
including over 1,300 lines of unprocessed agricultural products,
into the CEPT tariff reduction scheme.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN countries are now in a favorable position to take
advantage of surge of globalization and the liberalization of
investment and trade that are the hallmarks of the global economy
today.
</P>
<P>
To further complement international efforts to liberalize
trade, "we should impress upon all APEC member economies to submit
their action plans for the implementation of trade and investment
liberalization in the region," said the Thai foreign minister.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed the hope that by the APEC economic leaders
meeting in Manila in November this year, ASEAN will have credible
and feasible action plans.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
