<DOCNO> XIE19960721.0187 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Wins First Match at Olympic Volleyball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 20 (Xinhua) -- World Cup third finisher Chinese
women's team defeated European champion the Netherlands 3-0 in its
first group match at the 26th Olympic Games volleyball event here
this morning.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, under the guidance of former ace spiker Lang
Ping, routed the Dutch side 15-10, 15-5, 15-7 in 45 minutes of
play at the Omni Coliseum.
</P>
<P>
With hard spikes and tight net blockings, the Chinese players
dominated the match and spiked all the way to take the first set
quickly and then followed to wrap up the second set. Only in the
third set, the two teams had a hard fight before the Chinese
finally winning the match.
</P>
<P>
Chinese head coach Lang Ping said after the match she was
satisfied with her players' performance in their fourth encourter
against the Dutch players.
</P>
<P>
In their previous four encounters, the Chinese side won all the
matches when Lang Ping started to coach the team earlier last
year.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team was drawn in Group A together with host the
United States, one of the top favorites at the current games,
former volleyball powerhouse Japan, Ukraine, which competes in the
Olympics for the first time, and South Korea.
</P>
<P>
In their second match, the Chinese team will meet their old
rival South Korea on July 22. 
</P>
</TEXT>
