<HEADLINE> Italian Beats Defending Champion in Olympic Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Italian marksman Roberto Di Donna
beat defending champion Wang Yifu of China to take the men's 10
meters air pistol title here on Saturday at the Olympic shooting
competition.
</P>
<P>
The Italian, ranked third after the preliminaries with 585
points, scored 99.2 points in the 10-shot final and registered
684.2 points in grand total for the gold medal.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yifu, who won the event at the Barcelona Olympics four
years ago, led the field of 50 shooters from more than 30
countries and regions with 587 points in the preliminaries,
setting a new Olympic Games record.
</P>
<P>
As a four-time Olympian, Wang continued his lead after nine
shots in the shoot-off. But in the final shot, Wang, who was in
bad health in the last few weeks, only managed to score 6.5
points, 0.1 point less than the winner in the grand total.
</P>
<P>
Tanu Kiriakov of Bulgaria took the bronze medal with a total
of 683.8 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
